# Core Standards

- Keep changes scoped to the request and avoid speculative large builds.
- Respect monorepo boundaries: `apps/web`, `apps/backend`, and `supabase/*`.
- Preserve the source-link ingestion model. Store URLs and parsed data, not PDF binaries.
- Run the relevant lint, typecheck, and test commands after substantive edits.
- Update docs, env examples, and tests when contracts or workflows change.
- Do not add secrets, generated binaries, or unexplained schema changes to the repo.
- Record major technical decisions in `docs/adr`.
